{"timestamp": "2026-04-13T16:50:42.245509Z", "level": "INFO", "logger": "resume_parser", "message": "\ud83c\udfaf MODEL PARSED ENTITIES", "request_id": "a976685b-7aaa-40a7-8fc9-237808819772", "work_experience": [{"job_title": "Humana:   Current (Location: Louisville, KY)", "company_name": "Role: Senior Java Developer", "location": "", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": true, "clients": [], "description": "Responsibilities: Architected enterprise-grade Spring Boot microservices deployed on AWS ECS and EKS, implementing HIPAA-compliant RESTful APIs for healthcare claims processing, clinical records ingestion, and patient data management across HL7 FHIR interfaces. Designed agentic retrieval workflows using Java, LangChain, and LangGraph to build context-aware agents ingesting PR metadata, commit metadata, and GitHub history, enabling automated CES scoring and quality metric computation for healthcare pipelines. Migrated legacy Apache Airflow orchestration to Dagster across 40 production pipelines processing healthcare claims, clinical records, and patient data on AWS ECS and EKS, implementing retries, backfills, scheduling, and data quality alerts exposed through Power BI and Collibra. Built LLM-driven scoring systems using DSPy and Java backend services, integrating prompt optimization and context packing to automate healthcare PR-level scoring using GPT-4, AWS SageMaker, and MLflow for model versioning under HIPAA-compliant governance. Engineered Java Spring Boot backend services with AWS Lambda, AWS EventBridge, and AWS CDK to ingest PR and commit metadata from GitHub and Jenkins, computing CES metrics and exposing results through RESTful APIs and Power BI dashboards under HIPAA compliance. Orchestrated large-scale backfills using Dagster and AWS Glue, processing over 10 million commits and clinical record deltas with batching, caching, and DSPy-based score optimization, with data quality alerts in AWS CloudWatch and Collibra lineage tracking. Implemented SonarQube integration for Java codebase quality scoring, linking static analysis results with GitHub PR metadata to enrich CES metrics, and building Jira-integrated workflows for epicwork-type classification under HIPAA-compliant metadata governance. Developed AIML pipelines using Java ML integrations and MLLIB to predict patient readmission risk, implementing clinical decision support with LLMs, processing unstructured EHR data, and deploying inference infrastructure on AWS EC2 with HIPAAHITECH compliance. Deployed AWS CDK infrastructure-as-code for Java microservices on EC2, EKS, Lambda, and S3, automating provisioning, monitoring, and scaling of Dagster orchestrators, LLM inference endpoints, and AWS Glue jobs ensuring HIPAA compliance. Implemented conversational AI chatbots using LLMs and Java-based AWS EC2 services to automate patient triage and scheduling, integrating with EHR systems through secure API gateways with HIPAA privacy and HITECH compliance. Environment: Java 1117, Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, Hibernate, JPA, AWS SageMaker, AWS Lambda, Dagster, Jira, Collibra, NumPy, ERWIN, Pandas, MLflow, MLLIB, AWS EC2, AWS RDS, S3, DSPy, Jenkins, EventBridge, Git, AWS EKS, LangGraph, AWS CDK, GitHub, Power BI, LangChain, Glue, Airflow, ECS, SonarQube, Python, Docker, Kubernetes\nMorgan St"}], "education": [{"institution": "Lakshmaiah University", "degree": "Bachelor of Technology", "field_of_study": "Computer Science", "start_year": null, "end_year": null, "grade": null, "source": "rule_based_fallback"}]}
