emented SonarQube integration for Java codebase quality scoring, linking static analysis results with GitHub PR metadata to enrich CES metrics, and building Jira-integrated workflows for epicwork-type classification under HIPAA-compliant metadata governance. Developed AIML pipelines using Java ML integrations and MLLIB to predict patient readmission risk, implementing clinical decision support with LLMs, processing unstructured EHR data, and deploying inference infrastructure on AWS EC2 with HIPAAHITECH compliance. Deployed AWS CDK infrastructure-as-code for Java microservices on EC2, EKS, Lambda, and S3, automating provisioning, monitoring, and scaling of Dagster orchestrators, LLM inference endpoints, and AWS Glue jobs ensuring HIPAA compliance. Implemented conversational AI chatbots using LLMs and Java-based AWS EC2 services to automate patient triage and scheduling, integrating with EHR systems through secure API gateways with HIPAA privacy and HITECH compliance. Environment: Java 1117, Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, Hibernate, JPA, AWS SageMaker, AWS Lambda, Dagster, Jira, Collibra, NumPy, ERWIN, Pandas, MLflow, MLLIB, AWS EC2, AWS RDS, S3, DSPy, Jenkins, EventBridge, Git, AWS EKS, LangGraph, AWS CDK, GitHub, Power BI, LangChain, Glue, Airflow, ECS, SonarQube, Python, Docker, Kubernetes\nMorgan St"}], "education": [{"institution": "Lakshmaiah University", "degree": "Bachelor of Technology", "field_of_study": "Computer Science", "start_year": null, "end_year": null, "grade": null, "source": "rule_based_fallback"}]}
