{"timestamp": "2026-04-14T12:14:30.573345Z", "level": "INFO", "logger": "resume_parser", "message": "\ud83c\udfaf MODEL PARSED ENTITIES", "request_id": "82d731e4-541c-4ef1-8b4e-9a184ff82f32", "work_experience": [{"job_title": "Humana:   Present (Location: Louisville, KY)", "company_name": "Role: Sr. Python  Big Data Engineer", "location": "", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": true, "clients": [], "description": "Responsibilities: Designed and deployed agentic retrieval workflows using Python, LangChain, and LangGraph to build context-\naware AI agents ingesting PR metadata, commit metadata, and GitHub history, enabling automated CES scoring and\ncode quality metric computation for healthcare pipelines while ensuring HIPAA-compliant audit trails and HL7\ninteroperability across AWS S3, Lambda, and Glue. Built production-grade LLM-driven scoring systems using DSPy, integrating prompt optimization, chaining, and\ncontext packing to automate healthcare PR-level scoring, leveraging GPT-4, Claude, AWS Sagemaker, and MLflow\nfor model versioning, eval set generation, and feedback loops under HIPAA-compliant governance. Migrated legacy orchestration from Apache Airflow to Dagster across 40 production pipelines processing healthcare\nclaims, clinical records, and patient data on AWS ECS and EKS, implementing retries, backfills, scheduling, and data\nquality alerts with Power BI and Collibra reporting frameworks. Engineered backend services using Python, AWS Lambda, EventBridge, and AWS CDK to ingest PR and commit\nmetadata from GitHub and Jenkins, linking artifacts to compute CES metrics, quality signals, and anomalies while\nexposing results through RESTful APIs and Power BI dashboards under HIPAA compliance. Developed data modeling frameworks using Pandas, NumPy, and MLlib to link PRs, commits, branches, and epics\nfor healthcare software delivery metrics, building graph-based relationships across Jira, GitHub, and AWS S3, implementing anomaly detection, role classification, and effort estimation for HIPAA-compliant reporting. Orchestrated large-scale backfills and historical corrections using Dagster and AWS Glue, processing over 10 million\ncommits and clinical record deltas with batching, caching, and DSPy-based score optimization, ensuring data quality\nalerts captured in AWS CloudWatch and Collibra lineage tracking. Implemented SonarQube integration for code-quality scoring, linking static analysis results with GitHub PR metadata\nand commit history to enrich CES metrics, while building Jira-integrated workflows for epicwork-type classification\nand automated tagging under HIPAA-compliant metadata governance. Developed and deployed AIML pipelines using MLlib and NumPy to predict patient readmission risk, orchestrated\nwith Airflow for ingestion, transformation, and model retraining, ensuring HIPAA-compliant data handling and HL7\ninteroperability with comprehensive audit trails in alignment with HITECH Act regulations. Built observability and monitoring solutions using AWS CloudWatch, Lambda, and Dagster asset sensors to track\nmetrics, traces, logs, and data quality alerts across healthcare ETL pipelines, enabling automated alerting for failures, anomaly detection, and SLA breaches with Collibra and ERWIN lineage tracking. Engineered AIML clinical decision s"}], "education": [{"institution": "Lakshmaiah University", "degree": "Bachelor of Technology", "field_of_study": "Computer Science", "start_year": null, "end_year": null, "grade": null, "source": "rule_based_fallback"}]}
