{"timestamp": "2026-04-14T13:50:21.069927Z", "level": "INFO", "logger": "resume_parser", "message": "SUMMARY\n-------\n\nSenior Java Full Stack Developer with 11 years of\n\nEXPERIENCE\n----------\n\nworking on enterprise applications across healthcare, banking, retail, and aviation domains, involved in analysis, development, integration, deployment, and production support throughout the software development lifecycle, supporting systems used by large user bases and business-critical operations. Designed and developed enterprise-grade applications using Core Java, Java EE, Spring Boot, Spring MVC, and Spring Data integrated with SQL and NoSQL databases to build scalable backend systems supporting high-performance microservices architectures with comprehensive security controls across distributed environments. Architected RESTful APIs and microservices using Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, Core Java, and Docker deployed on AWS to enable modular enterprise applications with robust error handling, comprehensive logging, API versioning, and seamless communication between distributed services. Integrated AI and ML capabilities using Spring AI, LLM integrations, and Java EE frameworks to enhance business intelligence through secure data pipelines connecting application layers with AI services, managing model inference endpoints with Redis caching and asynchronous processing patterns. Implemented cloud-native solutions on AWS, Azure, and GCP platforms using Core Java, Spring Boot microservices, Kubernetes orchestration, and Docker containers leveraging managed SQL databases, messaging queues, and serverless functions with optimized resource utilization. Led technical architecture design using Java EE, Spring Boot, Spring MVC, microservices patterns, and PostgreSQL databases to create high-availability systems translating business requirements into robust implementations while mentoring teams and establishing coding standards throughout development lifecycle. Developed CICD pipelines using DevOps tools, Docker, Kubernetes, and Spring Boot applications integrated with AWS services to automate build, test, and deployment processes with containerization strategies and externalized configuration management across multiple environments. Built RESTful API architectures using Core Java, Spring MVC, Spring Boot, AI service integrations, and LLM capabilities deployed on Azure to create intelligent endpoints processing natural\n\nLANGUAGES\n---------\n\ninputs with authentication, authorization, rate limiting, and performance monitoring solutions. Designed database architectures supporting SQL databases including Oracle, PostgreSQL, MySQL and NoSQL databases like MongoDB, Cassandra, Redis integrated with Spring Data repositories and Java EE persistence layers ensuring data consistency through transaction management and event-driven architectures. Optimized application performance for Spring Boot and Java EE applications using microservices frameworks by conducting profiling, implementing Redis caching strategies, tuning JVM parameters, integrating Docker containerization, and establishing monitoring solutions tracking metrics and resource utilization. Implemented AI-driven workflows using Spring AI framework, ML model integration, and LLM services within Core Java applications deployed on GCP to automate processes, enable intelligent document processing, build conversational interfaces with model versioning and fallback mechanisms. Developed secure applications using Core Java, Java EE, Spring Security, OAuth2 protocols, and Spring Boot integrated with AWS, Azure, GCP platforms implementing authentication frameworks, role-based access controls, JWT tokens, encryption, and regulatory compliance standards. Built microservices infrastructure using Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, Docker, Kubernetes deployed on AWS with service discovery, load balancing, circuit breaker patterns, NoSQL databases, distributed configuration management, and ELK stack logging for comprehensive observability. Mentored development teams on Java development, Spring Boot, Spring MVC, microservices design patterns, AI integration strategies, and LLM techniques while conducting code reviews, leading technical workshops, establishing documentation practices, and ensuring adherence to standards. Translated business requirements into solutions using Core Java, Spring Boot, Spring Data, RESTful APIs, and PostgreSQL databases by collaborating with cross-functional teams, designing modular components with Docker containerization supporting evolving needs throughout the software development lifecycle. Implemented DevOps practices using CICD pipelines, Docker, Kubernetes, Spring Boot Test framework, and Azure platform to automate deployment workflows with infrastructure as code, automated testing strategies, MongoDB integration, and comprehensive monitoring and alerting systems.\n\nSKILLS\n------\n\nBackend  Core Technologies: Java (8111721), Core Java, J2EE, Spring Boot, Spring MVC, Spring Framework, Hibernate, JDBC, JMS, REST APIs, SOAP Web Services, Microservices, Multithreading, Jersey, Node.js, Scala, Python\nFrontend Technologies: HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, TypeScript, Angular, ReactJS, Bootstrap, jQuery, AJAX\nData, Configuration  Formats: XML, JSON, YAML, XSLT, XPath, SAX, DOM\nDatabases: Oracle, PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQL Server, MongoDB, Cassandra\nMessaging  Streaming  Security: Apache Kafka, RabbitMQ, JMS, Amazon SQS, Spring Security, OAuth 2.0, JWT\nDevOps, CICD  Build Tools: Docker, Kubernetes, OpenShift, Terraform, Maven, Ant, Jenkins, GitHub Actions\nTesting Tools: JUnit, TestNG, Mockito, Cucumber, Jest, Enzyme, JMeter, Postman, SoapUI, Cypress\nCloud Platforms: Amazon Web Services (AWS), Microsoft Azure, Google Cloud Platform (GCP)\nAI  Developer Productivity Tools: GitHub Copilot, LLM\nVersion Control  Operating Systems: Git, GitHub, GitLab, SVN, Linux, UNIX, Windows\nApplication Servers  Methodologies: Apache Tomcat, IBM WebSphere, WebLogic, JBoss Agile, Waterfall, TDD, SDLC\nIDEs  Development Tools: Eclipse, IntelliJ IDEA, Visual Studio Code (VS Code), IBM RAD, NetBeans\n\nEXPERIENCE\n----------\n\nUnitedHealth Group: May 2023 - Current (Location: Basking Ridge, NJ)\nSenior Java Full Stack Developer\nDesigned HIPAA-compliant healthcare applications using Core Java, Spring Boot, and Spring MVC with RESTful APIs for patient records and appointment scheduling, deploying microservices on Azure Virtual Machines integrated with Azure SQL Database and PostgreSQL for transactional persistence. Built HL7 FHIR-based interoperability RESTful APIs using Spring Boot and Spring Security with OAuth 2.0 and JWT tokens for role-based access control, connecting EHR systems with Azure SQL Database and documenting endpoints using Swagger for governance. Integrated AIML clinical decision support by embedding LLM models using Spring AI and LangChain frameworks, orchestrating workflows through Azure Functions with TensorFlow and PyTorch inference engines, storing outputs in Azure Cosmos DB for real-time insights. Developed microservices architecture using Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, and Apache Kafka for asynchronous messaging, implementing service discovery and circuit breakers with Docker containerization, ensuring high availability across Azure Kubernetes Service for healthcare transaction processing. Designed NoSQL data models in MongoDB and Azure Cosmos DB for unstructured clinical data alongside SQL schemas in PostgreSQL and Azure SQL Database for billing workflows, optimizing queries using Core Java for high-throughput operations and data consistency. Led code reviews enforcing Core Java and Spring Boot standards, implementing static analysis with SonarQube, ensuring JUnit and Mockito unit testing coverage, validating HIPAA compliance through Spring Security controls including data masking and secure Logback logging. Built CICD pipelines using Jenkins and Azure DevOps automating Spring Boot application deployments as Docker containers on Azure Kubernetes Service, provisioning Azure Virtual Machines, Azure SQL Database, and Azure Monitor using Terraform for infrastructure management. Enhanced patient portals developing responsive interfaces using Angular, React.js, and Next.js integrated with Spring Boot and Spring MVC backend RESTful APIs, implementing Spring Security for session management protecting PHI per HIPAA accessibility standards. Integrated Azure OpenAI Service and LangChain with Spring AI for automated medical coding workflows, processing physician input using LLM models to generate ICD-10 and CPT codes, reducing manual effort while maintaining CMS compliance and audit controls. Optimized performance implementing monitoring using Prometheus, Grafana, and Azure Monitor, analyzing JVM metrics and database query performance in PostgreSQL and Azure SQL Database, resolving memory leaks and latency issues maintaining 99.9 uptime for Spring Boot applications. Developed ETL pipelines using Azure Data Factory, Azure Databricks, and Apache Kafka ingesting HL7 messages and FHIR resources, storing processed data in Azure Synapse Analytics with MongoDB intermediate storage ensuring HIPAA audit compliance and data lineage validation. Mentored developers on Core Java, Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, Spring Data, and Spring Security best practices for microservices design, RESTful API development, and AIML integration strategies for secure PHI handling through knowledge-sharing sessions and pair programming. Implemented authentication using Spring Security integrated with Azure Active Directory for single sign-on and multi-factor authentication, enforcing role-based access control with OAuth 2.0 and JWT tokens, logging all access events satisfying HIPAA security and privacy rules. Built predictive analytics integrating TensorFlow and PyTorch models with Spring Boot microservices, exposing inference via RESTful APIs stored in Azure Cosmos DB and PostgreSQL, enabling risk stratification while maintaining HIPAA data anonymization and de-identification guidelines. Implemented event-driven architecture using Apache Kafka streaming real-time patient vitals across microservices, ensuring data consistency through Kafka Connect integrations with PostgreSQL, MongoDB, and Azure Cosmos DB maintaining message encryption for PHI compliance and fault tolerance. Developed Docker and Kubernetes containerized deployments for Spring Boot applications on Azure Kubernetes Service, configuring pod autoscaling and health checks with Azure Monitor, ensuring disaster recovery for patient admissions and billing integrations using Jenkins automation pipelines. Environment: LangChain, Core Java, spring cloud, JUnit, Virtual Machines, SQL, Apache Kafka, prometheus, Spring AI, jira, Python, Data Factory, Java EE, TensorFlow, PyTorch, Spring Boot, Databricks, Selenium, CICD, Next.js, NoSQL, swagger, Azure SQL Database, Blob Storage, Spring MVC, PostgreSQL, Docker, git, Kubernetes, angular, Cosmos DB, maven, grafana, logback, Azure, Spring Security, Spring Data, MongoDB, springboot, jenkins, terrraform, Synapse Analytics, Functions, React.js\nBNY Mellon: July 2020 - April 2023 (Location: New York, NY)\nSenior Full Stack Developer\nDeveloped enterprise banking applications using Core Java, Java EE, and Spring Boot to process high-volume transactions, deployed on AWS EC2 and EKS, implementing RESTful APIs with Spring MVC for core banking system integration while ensuring PCI-DSS compliance and comprehensive Log4j audit logging. Built microservices for loan origination and fraud detection using Spring Boot, Spring Data, and OAuth2 authentication, deployed on AWS Lambda and EKS, integrating RabbitMQ message broker for event-driven architecture and connecting backend services through secure RESTful APIs with React.js frontend dashboards. Architected payment processing systems using Java EE, Spring Boot, and AWS SQS for real-time fund transfers, implementing Oracle and DynamoDB databases for transactional storage, configured Spring Security with OAuth2 protocols, and maintained PCI-DSS compliance through encryption and role-based access controls. Integrated AI capabilities into credit risk assessment by connecting Core Java backend with AWS SageMaker machine learning services, exposing insights through Spring Boot RESTful APIs consumed by React.js applications, utilizing Spring Data for model data persistence and Mockito for comprehensive unit testing coverage. Designed cloud-native solutions on AWS utilizing EC2, RDS, S3, Lambda, and Redshift, implementing infrastructure as code with CloudFormation, configured EKS for Kubernetes orchestration, established CloudWatch monitoring, and deployed Spring Boot microservices through CICD pipelines using GitHub Actions and Docker containerization. Developed customer-facing portals using React.js and Next.js integrated with Spring Boot backend via RESTful APIs secured by OAuth2, implementing Spring MVC controllers for account management workflows, storing session data in DynamoDB, and ensuring PCI-DSS compliance through Spring Security configurations and encryption protocols. Implemented DevOps practices using GitHub Actions for CICD pipelines, containerized applications with Docker and Podman, orchestrated deployments on AWS EKS Kubernetes clusters, utilized Ansible for configuration management, and automated Spring Boot application builds using Gradle with zero-downtime production releases. Created automated testing frameworks using Mockito for Java unit tests, Cucumber for behavior-driven integration testing of Spring Boot services, validated RESTful APIs with Postman, tested React.js components, and achieved comprehensive coverage across microservices deployed on AWS Lambda ensuring regulatory compliance standards. Optimized performance by tuning Spring Boot services and SQL queries on Oracle databases, implemented caching strategies using Spring framework capabilities, configured connection pooling for DynamoDB and Cassandra NoSQL databases, analyzed bottlenecks through ELK Stack monitoring, and reduced latency for high-frequency banking transactions. Configured centralized logging using ELK Stack with Elasticsearch, Logstash, and Kibana for distributed microservices, implemented structured Log4j logging standards across Spring Boot applications, integrated with AWS CloudWatch for real-time monitoring, and maintained audit trails meeting SOX compliance requirements for incident response protocols. Developed batch processing jobs using Spring Boot, AWS Lambda, and EMR for end-of-day reconciliation and statement generation, scheduled executions with AWS CloudWatch Events, utilized Gradle for build automation, processed large datasets from S3 storage, and monitored job completion through CloudWatch dashboards ensuring data accuracy. Built ETL pipelines using AWS Glue, Lambda, and S3 for processing transaction files from partner banks, implemented Java transformation logic within Spring Boot services, applied encryption protocols meeting PCI-DSS standards, integrated DynamoDB for metadata management, and validated data quality through automated Mockito test suites. Integrated legacy systems with modern microservices using SOAP and RESTful APIs, implemented adapter patterns with Java EE and Spring Boot, maintained data integrity across Oracle databases and AWS RDS, configured Spring Data repositories, and enabled gradual modernization while ensuring backward compatibility through comprehensive Cucumber integration testing. Mentored developers on Core Java, Spring Boot, Spring MVC, Spring Data, and microservices patterns, conducted code reviews for RESTful APIs using GitHub, provided guidance on AWS cloud services including EC2 and Lambda, led sessions on OAuth2 security implementations, and enhanced team capabilities in Docker containerization and Kubernetes orchestration. Created business intelligence solutions using AWS Redshift, Athena, and Glue for transaction analytics, developed Spring Boot RESTful APIs serving aggregated data to React.js visualization dashboards, optimized SQL queries for reporting performance, stored analytical datasets in S3, and enabled data-driven decision making through ELK Stack operational metrics monitoring. Enhanced security by implementing multi-factor authentication using Spring Security and OAuth2, configured AWS IAM policies for access management, applied encryption at rest in DynamoDB and Oracle databases, conducted vulnerability assessments across Java applications and microservices, and maintained PCI-DSS compliance through continuous security monitoring with CloudWatch alerts. Environment: Java, DynamoDB, Athena, RabbitMQ, GitHub, Core Java, elk stack, SQS, CloudWatch, Cassandra, Java EE, confluence, EC2, Lambda, CloudFormation, github actions, OAuth2, ansible, react, Spring Boot, SNS, EMR, RDS, Spring Data, NoSQL, log4j, Spring MVC, cucumber, Kubernetes, EKS, Redshift, Mockito, helidon, S3, Next.js, soap, springboot, IAM, VPC, React.js, AWS, Oracle, Glue, SQL, Docker, postman, podman, gradle\nTarget: September 2017 - June 2020 (Location: Minneapolis, MN)\nJava developer\nDesigned and developed enterprise-grade Java applications for retail platforms using Core Java, Spring Boot, Spring MVC, and Spring Data JPA to process millions of daily transactions with RESTful APIs and microservices architecture deployed on AWS EC2 instances. Built scalable microservices using Spring Boot integrated with AWS RDS, AWS S3, AWS Lambda, and DynamoDB to support retail operations while implementing RESTful APIs and GraphQL endpoints ensuring PCI-DSS compliance for payment processing workflows. Architected high-availability systems using Docker containerization and Kubernetes orchestration on AWS EKS and OpenShift, establishing CICD pipelines with GitLab CI and Helm charts to automate Spring Boot microservices deployments with zero-downtime releases. Integrated MySQL, MongoDB, AWS RDS, and DynamoDB databases using Spring Data JPA to manage retail product catalogs, customer profiles, and inventory with optimized query performance ensuring PCI-DSS compliant encryption and GDPR data privacy. Led code reviews enforcing Java and Spring Boot best practices, mentored developers on Core Java design patterns and microservices architecture, and conducted technical sessions translating retail business requirements into scalable solutions adhering to GDPR compliance. Implemented DevOps practices using GitLab CI, Docker, Kubernetes, and AWS CloudFormation to automate Java microservices deployments on AWS EKS, provisioning AWS IAM, VPC, EC2, and RDS resources with infrastructure-as-code. Developed RESTful APIs and GraphQL services using Spring Boot and OpenAPI specifications integrated with Angular and React.js frontends, implementing JWT authentication ensuring PCI-DSS and GDPR compliance for retail payment operations. Optimized application performance using Splunk for logging, AWS CloudWatch for monitoring, and SLF4J for structured logs across Spring Boot microservices, tuning JVM parameters and implementing caching strategies for high-volume retail transaction processing. Built asynchronous messaging systems using ActiveMQ and AWS SNSSQS integrated with Spring Boot microservices to support event-driven retail workflows including order processing, inventory updates, and customer notifications ensuring transactional consistency across distributed systems. Collaborated with cross-functional teams translating retail requirements into technical solutions using Java EE and Spring Boot, providing guidance on microservices architecture, RESTful API design, and AWS infrastructure decisions aligned with business objectives. Implemented testing strategies using JUnit for unit tests, Cypress for end-to-end tests, and Maven for builds ensuring Java microservices quality with integration testing for RESTful APIs and performance testing under retail load conditions. Configured AWS Lambda serverless functions integrated with Spring Boot microservices for event-driven workflows, utilizing AWS Glue, AWS Athena, and AWS EMR for data transformation pipelines supporting retail business intelligence and analytics initiatives. Enhanced security implementing AWS IAM policies, VPC isolation, and encryption across AWS RDS and DynamoDB ensuring PCI-DSS compliance and GDPR requirements with TLSSSL\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\n--------------\n\nand audit controls protecting retail customer data. Integrated Slack notifications with CICD pipelines and AWS CloudWatch monitoring providing real-time visibility into Spring Boot deployments, configuring automated alerts for API response times, error rates, and AWS resource utilization metrics. Migrated legacy monolithic retail applications to microservices architecture using Spring Boot, Docker, and Kubernetes, implementing API Gateway patterns and service mesh technologies ensuring backward compatibility and continuous availability during phased migration. Developed data pipelines using AWS Redshift, AWS Glue, and AWS Athena aggregating retail data from MySQL, MongoDB, and DynamoDB, creating Spring Boot batch jobs and AWS Lambda scheduled tasks for transformations and business reporting. Environment: Slf4j, Restful Apis, Core Java, Openshift, AWS, Springboot, Lambda, Spring Boot, Junit, Java, Nosql, Helm, Kubernetes, RDS, Splunk, Dynamodb, EKS, IAM, Cloudwatch, Athena, SQL, Angular, VPC, Glue, React.Js, Mongodb, EMR, Graph Ql, Open Api, SNS, Redshift, S3, Cypress, Spring MVC, SQS, Mysql, Maven, Java EE, EC2, Active Mq, Gitlab Ci, Cloudformation, Gitlab, Next.Js, Docker, Spring Data, JWT, Quarkus\nSouthwest Airlines: January 2016 - August 2017 (Location: Dallas, TX)\nBackend Developer\nDesigned, developed, and maintained backend microservices using Java 8, Spring Boot, and Microservices architecture, supporting OpsSuite, a real-time airline operations platform used by ramp agents and operations teams across more than one hundred airport locations, ensuring reliable processing of operational events and system responsiveness. Built and secured RESTful APIs using Spring Security and Apigee API Management, enforcing authentication, authorization, and API governance standards, while ensuring protected and reliable communication between backend services and external consumers within the real-time airline operations ecosystem. Worked extensively with relational databases using PostgreSQL hosted on GCP Cloud SQL, managing schema design, data modeling, query tuning, and database administration with pgAdmin, while developing PLSQL procedures to support transactional consistency and operational data processing. Implemented service discovery and load management using Spring Cloud, enabling reliable inter-service communication, improved fault tolerance, and scalable backend interactions across a distributed microservices environment supporting real-time airline operations and scheduling workflows. Developed asynchronous and event-driven communication using RabbitMQ, enabling decoupled messaging, real-time data flow, and reliable event processing between backend services, improving system responsiveness and coordination across operational components within the OpsSuite platform. Containerized backend services using Docker and deployed them to Kubernetes platforms including GKE and OpenShift, ensuring consistent runtime environments, scalable service orchestration, and controlled deployments across development, testing, and production environments. Automated infrastructure provisioning and configuration management using Terraform on Google Compute Engine and other GCP Cloud resources, supporting consistent environment creation, deployment repeatability, and reliable backend infrastructure for mission-critical airline operations systems. Supported CICD pipelines using Jenkins, Maven, and Git, enabling automated builds, testing, and deployments, while integrating backend services into continuous delivery workflows aligned with Agile development practices managed through Jira. Ensured backend quality and performance through rigorous testing and analysis using JUnit, Mockito, and Postman, while performing in-depth performance profiling with JProfiler to identify memory usage issues and bottlenecks, maintaining high availability and stability during peak operational conditions. Environment: Java 8, Spring Boot, Microservices, Restful API, PostgreSQL, pgAdmin, PLSQL, Agile, JavaScript, Git, Spring Cloud, Maven, Spring Security, Jenkins, Jira, RabbitMQ, Docker, Kubernetes, Junit, Terraform, Hibernate, Postman, Mockito, GKE, Google compute engine, GCP Cloud, GCP Cloud SQL, Apigee API Management, Maven, OpenShift, Jprofiler\nRamco Systems: August 2014 - October 2015 (Location: Chennai, India)\nBackend Developer\nWorked on enterprise-grade Java applications built on Java 8, J2EE, and Spring MVC, contributing across design, development, and maintenance phases while supporting complex business workflows, multi-layered architectures, and long-running transactional processes used by large enterprise customers. Applied core design patterns including Singleton, Factory, DAO, Business Delegate, Session Facade, and Value Object, improving code maintainability and reusability while reducing duplication and enforcing consistent design practices across service, persistence, and presentation layers in large-scale, multi-module Java-based enterprise systems. Implemented Spring Framework features such as IoC, Dependency Injection, and Spring AOP to manage cross-cutting concerns and service wiring, improving modularity, reducing tight coupling, and enabling clearer separation of responsibilities across backend components within layered enterprise application architectures. Developed server-side components using Servlets, JSP, Struts, JSTL, and JavaScript, integrating backend services with presentation layers while ensuring stable request handling, proper input validation, session management, and secure interaction with downstream systems operating in enterprise production environments. Used Hibernate ORM and HQL to manage database interactions with Microsoft SQL Server, writing optimized queries, managing schema changes, and improving data access performance by 25, while ensuring transactional integrity, reliable persistence, and consistent data handling across backend workflows. Built and tested web services using SOAP, WSDL, JAX-B, XML, JMS, and JNDI, supporting integration with external systems, message-driven processing, and synchronous communication patterns commonly required in enterprise service-oriented architectures and distributed application environments. Supported application quality and stability through JUnit unit testing, Log4J logging, and structured debugging practices, while managing source control with SVN and development using Eclipse and IBM WebSphere, contributing to improved collaboration and a 30 reduction in code conflicts across development teams. Environment: Java 8, JSP, Spring MVC, Servlets, JavaScript, Hibernate, Microsoft SQL Server, HTML5, CSS, Scrum, WSDL, SOAP, JAX-B, Log4j, XML, JNDI, JMS, JSTL, RMI, Struts, Generics, Multithreading, JML, Azure Repos, Azure Functions, Amazon SNS, Spring AOP, WebLogic, SQL, JUnit, SVN, Log4J, IBM WebSphere\n\nEDUCATION\n---------\n\nBachelor of Technology in Computer Science - MLWE college - June 2010 - July 2014", "request_id": "52e5a8a2-f68a-4ffe-a01e-af0e7a150bb9"}
