{"timestamp": "2026-04-14T13:50:27.345506Z", "level": "INFO", "logger": "resume_parser", "message": "\ud83c\udfaf MODEL PARSED ENTITIES", "request_id": "52e5a8a2-f68a-4ffe-a01e-af0e7a150bb9", "work_experience": [{"job_title": "UnitedHealth Group:  - Current (Location: Basking Ridge, NJ)", "company_name": "Senior Java Full Stack Developer", "location": "", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": true, "clients": [], "description": "Designed HIPAA-compliant healthcare applications using Core Java, Spring Boot, and Spring MVC with RESTful APIs for patient records and appointment scheduling, deploying microservices on Azure Virtual Machines integrated with Azure SQL Database and PostgreSQL for transactional persistence. Built HL7 FHIR-based interoperability RESTful APIs using Spring Boot and Spring Security with OAuth 2.0 and JWT tokens for role-based access control, connecting EHR systems with Azure SQL Database and documenting endpoints using Swagger for governance. Integrated AIML clinical decision support by embedding LLM models using Spring AI and LangChain frameworks, orchestrating workflows through Azure Functions with TensorFlow and PyTorch inference engines, storing outputs in Azure Cosmos DB for real-time insights. Developed microservices architecture using Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, and Apache Kafka for asynchronous messaging, implementing service discovery and circuit breakers with Docker containerization, ensuring high availability across Azure Kubernetes Service for healthcare transaction processing. Designed NoSQL data models in MongoDB and Azure Cosmos DB for unstructured clinical data alongside SQL schemas in PostgreSQL and Azure SQL Database for billing workflows, optimizing queries using Core Java for high-throughput operations and data consistency. Led code reviews enforcing Core Java and Spring Boot standards, implementing static analysis with SonarQube, ensuring JUnit and Mockito unit testing coverage, validating HIPAA compliance through Spring Security controls including data masking and secure Logback logging. Built CICD pipelines using Jenkins and Azure DevOps automating Spring Boot application deployments as Docker containers on Azure Kubernetes Service, provisioning Azure Virtual Machines, Azure SQL Database, and Azure Monitor using Terraform for infrastructure management. Enhanced patient portals developing responsive interfaces using Angular, React.js, and Next.js integrated with Spring Boot and Spring MVC backend RESTful APIs, implementing Spring Security for session management protecting PHI per HIPAA accessibility standards. Integrated Azure OpenAI Service and LangChain with Spring AI for automated medical coding workflows, processing physician input using LLM models to generate ICD-10 and CPT codes, reducing manual effort while maintaining CMS compliance and audit controls. Optimized performance implementing monitoring using Prometheus, Grafana, and Azure Monitor, analyzing JVM metrics and database query performance in PostgreSQL and Azure SQL Database, resolving memory leaks and latency issues maintaining 99.9 uptime for Spring Boot applications. Developed ETL pipelines using Azure Data Factory, Azure Databricks, and Apache Kafka ingesting HL7 messages and FHIR resources, storing processed data in Azure Synapse Analytic"}], "education": [{"institution": "MLWE college", "degree": "Bachelor of Technology", "field_of_study": "Computer Science", "start_year": null, "end_year": null, "grade": null, "source": "rule_based_fallback"}]}
