{"timestamp": "2026-04-14T13:59:14.504071Z", "level": "INFO", "logger": "resume_parser", "message": "SUMMARY\n-------\n\nDevelopment, Software Engineering, and Data Science. Skilled in building dynamic, data-driven web applications using Python, Java, Django, React, and Spring Boot, and experienced in analytical programming using NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib, and\nScikit-learn. Adept at designing full-stack systems, automating processes, and\ntranslating complex data into actionable insights. Seeking opportunities in Web\nDevelopment, Software Engineering, or Data Science domains to contribute to\nreal-world digital transformation\n\nPROJECTS\n--------\n\n. Programming\n\nLANGUAGES\n---------\n\n: Python, Java, C, JavaScript\n\nSKILLS\n------\n\nWeb Technologies: HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, Tailwind CSS, React.js, Django, Flask, JSP, Spring Boot, JDBC\nDatabases: MySQL, MongoDB Atlas (AWS), Oracle Live SQL\nData Science Tools: NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn, Scikit-learn, Gen AI\nConcepts\nCloud  Tools: AWS Cloud, GitHub, Postman, Visual Studio Code, IntelliJ IDEA, Eclipse, Jupyter Notebook, Google Colab\nOther\n\nSKILLS\n------\n\n: RESTful API integration, Responsive Web Design, Version Control, Data Analysis  Visualization\nWeb Developer  Data Science Intern\nINTERNSHIP\nSpider\n\nPROJECTS\n--------\n\nOne Jan 2024 - Jun 2024\nDeveloped and optimized responsive web applications using Django, Flask, and MongoDB, focusing on user interactivity and data eciency. Designed RESTful APIs to handle CRUD operations and seamless data\ncommunication between frontend and backend. Conducted data-driven feature development by integrating analytics modules\nand visualization dashboards. Deployed applications on AWS cloud, ensuring scalability and secure access\ncontrol. Built and integrated machine learning models for predictive features and\nimproved automation. Collaborated within an Agile team environment, utilizing Git for version control\nand continuous integration. Registration  Selling of Second-Hand Cars\n\nPROJECTS\n--------\n\nDeveloper\nBuilt a full-stack dynamic platform enabling users to list, search, and purchase\npre-owned vehicles securely. Implemented role-based authentication, real-time data updates, and a user-\nfriendly admin dashboard. Integrated payment simulation, messaging, and analytics modules to simulate\nend-to-end e-commerce operations. Enhanced system reliability by optimizing SQL queries and backend logic. Tech Stack: Python, Django, MySQL, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Bootstrap\nData Analytics Dashboard for Used Cars\nDeveloper\nExtended the car resale\n\nPROJECTS\n--------\n\nto include data-driven insights for market\npricing and user demand trends. Performed exploratory data analysis (EDA) using Pandas, NumPy, and Seaborn\nto extract key business insights. Designed interactive data visualizations and reports using Matplotlib and\nintegrated them with Django-based UI. Tech Stack: Python, Django, Pandas, Matplotlib, MySQL\nNet Bank Admin Application\nDeveloper\nDeveloped a comprehensive admin portal for managing customer accounts, transactions, and reporting activities. Applied Spring Boot and JSP frameworks for backend logic and frontend\nintegration, ensuring secure authentication and robust database operations. Integrated transaction logs and report generation features for administrative\ninsights. Tech Stack: Java, Spring Boot, JSP, MySQL\nProperty Dealer Management System\nDeveloper\nCreated a web-based property management platform for listing, searching, and managing property data. Implemented form validation, search lters, and responsive UI design to\nenhance usability. Integrated MySQL database for secure data storage and retrieval, ensuring\noptimized access and reliability. Tech Stack: Java, JSP, HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, MySQL\nMaster of Computer Applications (MCA)\n\nEDUCATION\n---------\n\nP.R. Pote Patil College of Engineering and Management, Sant Gadge Baba\nAmravati University\nJan 2022 - Jan 2024\nBachelor of Science (B.Sc.)\nG.S. Tompe Arts, Commerce and Science College, Sant Gadge Baba Amravati\nUniversity\nJan 2018 - Jan 2021\nData Science  AI Masters 2025  From Python to Gen AI\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\n--------------\n\nUdemy 23 Oct 2025\nPython for Data Science\nNPTEL\nPython for Web  Data Science\nSoham Global\nDatabase Management Essentials\nCoursera\nEnglish\n\nLANGUAGES\n---------\n\nHindi", "request_id": "a61efab7-4b20-4b6c-8fd2-942019da825b"}
