{"timestamp": "2026-04-14T14:22:13.597221Z", "level": "INFO", "logger": "resume_parser", "message": "SUMMARY\n-------\n\n- Over 11 years of diverse IT\n\nEXPERIENCE\n----------\n\nas a Java Full Stack\nDeveloper, proficient in Software Process Engineering, adept at\ndesigning and building Web Applications using JavaJ2EE and\nopen-source technologies. - Developed enterprise web applications using Java across multiple\n\nPROJECTS\n--------\n\n, implementing complex functionalities that reduced system\nprocessing time while maintaining robust application security and\nscalability for high-traffic environments with thousands of\nconcurrent users. - Designed database architectures supporting mission-critical\napplications, writing advanced SQL queries and stored procedures\nthat improved data retrieval efficiency while ensuring seamless\nintegration with Java persistence layers across distributed systems. - Created responsive user interfaces utilizing JavaScript frameworks\nfor enterprise-level applications, implementing custom solutions\nthat enhanced user\n\nEXPERIENCE\n----------\n\nthrough dynamic content loading while\nensuring cross-browser compatibility and accessibility standards. - Developed modular CSS styling systems for large-scale web\napplications, implementing responsive designs that maintained\nconsistent branding across multiple device types while reducing code\nredundancy and improving maintenance efficiency. - Built modern responsive interfaces using Bootstrap component\nlibraries for enterprise applications, customizing frameworks to\ncreate intuitive user experiences while maintaining accessibility\nstandards and ensuring consistent rendering across all major\nbrowsers. - Implemented data persistence layers using JPA for complex enterprise\napplications, designing efficient entity relationships and\noptimizing query performance while ensuring proper transaction\nmanagement and data integrity across distributed microservices. - Engineered web services and RESTful APIs using Java and Spring\nframework that processed millions of requests daily, implementing\ncomprehensive error handling while ensuring secure authentication\nprotocols and maintaining detailed API documentation. - Constructed complex database schemas and wrote optimized SQL queries\nsupporting multi-tenant architectures, designing efficient indexing\nstrategies and implementing advanced procedures that supported\ncomplex reporting requirements while maintaining sub-second query\nperformance. - Utilized Eclipse IDE for full-stack development across multiple\nenterprise\n\nPROJECTS\n--------\n\n, customizing workspaces with specialized plugins\nthat enhanced team productivity while establishing standardized code\nformatting and quality control processes. - Developed interactive web components using jQuery for enterprise\napplications, creating custom plugins that simplified complex DOM\nmanipulations while ensuring optimal performance and compatibility\nacross various browser environments. - Configured and deployed web applications on Apache Tomcat servers\nacross environments, implementing custom configurations that\noptimized memory usage and connection pooling while ensuring high\navailability through clustering. - Created comprehensive test suites using JUnit and Selenium for\nautomated testing of web applications, designing test cases that\nachieved comprehensive code coverage while implementing continuous\nintegration pipelines that enforced quality standards. - Implemented CICD pipelines using AWS cloud services including\nCodeCommit, CodeBuild, and CodeDeploy, configuring infrastructure as\ncode that automated deployment processes while ensuring consistent\nenvironment configurations across development stages. - Managed\n\nPROJECTS\n--------\n\nrequirements and sprint planning through Jira and\nConfluence, creating detailed workflows that improved team velocity\nwhile maintaining comprehensive technical documentation that\nfacilitated knowledge sharing across development teams. - Analyzed complex business requirements to determine appropriate\ntechnology solutions, translating stakeholder needs into technical\nspecifications while ensuring alignment with enterprise architecture\nstandards and identifying potential integration challenges. - Collaborated with cross-functional teams to design and implement web\nservices that met specific business requirements, facilitating\ntechnical discussions between development and business stakeholders\nwhile ensuring solutions met performance and security standards. - Investigated operational issues through detailed system analysis and\ntroubleshooting, identifying root causes of production problems\nwhile implementing permanent fixes that prevented recurrence and\ndocumenting solutions for future reference. - Communicated technical concepts effectively to non-technical users\nand stakeholders, creating clear documentation and presentations\nthat translated complex systems into understandable terms while\ngathering valuable feedback for continuous improvement.\n\nSKILLS\n------\n\nProgramming\n\nLANGUAGES\n---------\n\n: C, C, Java 11, SQL, PLSQL, Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, GoLang\nJavaJ2EE Technologies: Servlets, Spring, JSP, JSTL, JDBC, RMI, EJB, JFCSwing, AWT, Applets, Multi-threading, Java Networking\nFrameworks: Spring, Hibernate, Angular JS, Spring Security, Spring Boot, Spring MVC, Spring Data JPA, Spring Cloud (Netflix, Gateway), NgRx, Redux-Saga, Grunt\nWeb Technologies: JSP, JavaScript, jQuery, AJAX, Angular JS, Angular 2, XML, HTML5, CSS3, ReactJS, BackBone.JS, Node JS, Express JS, Redux, Tailwind CSS, Webpack, Babel\nRelational Database: Oracle 11g12C, SQL Server 201220142016, MySQL, PostgreSQL\nNoSQL Databases: MongoDB, Cassandra, DynamoDB, Redis\nWeb Services: SOAP 1.2, REST 2.0, JAX-WS, JAX-RPC, JAX-RS, Swagger, RESTful, GraphQL\nApplicationWeb Servers: Apache Tomcat 8.0, OracleBEA WebLogic, Apache\nCXF, IBM WebSphere\nMessaging: RabbitMQ, IBM MQ, Apache Kafka\nIDEs: Eclipse, IntelliJ 2017.1, Spring Tool Suite (STS) 3.9.3, Atom, PyCharm, Visual Studio\nCloud Environments: Azure, AWS, GCP, Netflix Eureka, Kubernetes, Elastic\nBeanstalk, Docker, OpenShift, MLops (MLairflow, DVC), RedHat, OpenShift\nMethodologies: Agile (SAFe 6.x), Waterfall, TDD\n(Test-Driven-Development), Scrum\nTesting TechnologiesTools: JUnit, Postman, TestNG, Mockito, Cucumber, JMeter, RFT, React Testing Library, Cypress, Jasmine, Karma, LEX\nVersion Control: Git, Bitbucket, SVN, Rational ClearCase\nBuild Tools: Maven 3.3.9, Gradle 3.4.1, Ant 1.10, Jenkins\nPlatforms: Windows 10, UNIX, Linux\nSecurity Technologies: OAuth2, JWT, Spring Security, HTTPS, TLS, AES\nPerformance and Monitoring Tools: Prometheus, Grafana, AWS CloudWatch, JVisualVM, Log4J, Logstash, Elasticsearch, Kibana, JIRA\n\nEXPERIENCE\n----------\n\nClient: Cigna Healthcare Bloomfield, CT\nSr. Full Stack Java Developer Dec 2021  Present\n- Developed secure healthcare data management system using Java and\nSpring Boot, creating RESTful microservices that integrated with\nlegacy systems while ensuring compliance through custom annotations\nfor data validation and sanitization. - Built comprehensive healthcare provider portal utilizing Spring MVC\nand Hibernate for seamless data persistence, enabling professionals\nto access records securely while implementing advanced caching\nstrategies that reduced database load during peak hours. - Created real-time monitoring dashboards with JavaScript and\nBootstrap, designing responsive interfaces that displayed critical\nmetrics and schedules with custom components specifically designed\nfor healthcare workflows. - Implemented continuous integration and deployment pipelines using\nAWS CodeBuild, AWS CodeDeploy, and Jenkins, enabling rapid delivery\nof application updates while configuring automated security scans\nand compliance checks before production deployment. - Maintained RESTful APIs with Swagger documentation for\ninteroperability between different healthcare systems, facilitating\nseamless data exchange between departments while implementing\nversioning strategies to ensure backward compatibility. - Executed comprehensive testing strategies using JUnit and Selenium, achieving over 90 code coverage for critical applications while\ndesigning custom extensions to simulate domain-specific scenarios\nfor robust workflow validation. - Optimized SQL queries and designed stored procedures in Oracle\ndatabases to enhance performance of healthcare record retrieval and\nbilling processes using advanced tuning techniques for high-volume\ntransactions. - Deployed containerized microservices using Docker and Kubernetes for\nscalable applications, ensuring high availability during peak hours\nwhile configuring health checks to monitor service dependencies. - Integrated OAuth authentication framework with AWS IAM to secure\nprotected information across multiple applications, implementing\ncustom policies to enforce least privilege access controls for\ndifferent user roles. - Configured logging and monitoring solutions using ELK Stack and AWS\nCloudWatch to track system performance and detect potential security\nbreaches, setting up custom alarms for critical metrics and\ncompliance issues. - Utilized DynamoDB and Amazon S3 to build scalable document storage\nsolution that supported quick retrieval of records while\nimplementing versioning to maintain complete history. - Developed healthcare inventory management system using Spring Data\nJPA and PostgreSQL, creating efficient data models for tracking\nsupplies across multiple locations with optimized repository\nmethods. - Implemented comprehensive logging with Log4j and Logback for audit\ntrails of all sensitive data access, ensuring compliance with\nregulations while creating custom appenders to format logs\nspecifically for compliance audits. - Managed version control using Git and AWS CodeCommit for application\ncodebases, implementing branch protection rules and code review\nprocesses while establishing workflows aligned with enterprise\nsoftware development requirements. - Integrated Postman and SonarQube into development workflow to ensure\nAPI testing coverage and code quality standards, creating automated\ntest collections that validated domain-specific data formats and\nregulatory compliance requirements. - Designed distributed caching solutions using Redis for applications, implementing cache invalidation strategies that maintained data\nconsistency while significantly reducing database load for\nfrequently accessed information. - Configured Apache Tomcat servers for web applications, optimizing\nJVM settings and connection pools to handle peak traffic while\nensuring proper session management for secure user access. - Implemented Microservices architecture, designing service boundaries\naround business domains while creating resilient communication\npatterns between services using circuit breakers and retry\nmechanisms. - Developed data migration strategies for legacy systems, creating ETL\nprocesses that preserved data integrity while transforming records\nto conform with modern data standards. - Implemented SOAP web services for integration with external\nhealthcare providers, creating secure message exchanges that\nmaintained data confidentiality while ensuring reliable delivery of\ncritical information. - Created comprehensive API Gateway solutions using AWS API Gateway\nfor microservices, implementing request throttling and\nauthentication mechanisms while providing unified access points for\nmobile and web applications. - Developed batch processing systems for healthcare claims using\nSpring Batch, implementing job partitioning strategies that\noptimized processing of large datasets while maintaining detailed\nexecution logs for audit purposes. Environment: Amazon EKS, AWS CodeDeploy, Amazon S3, AWS CodeBuild, AWS\nIAM, AWS SNS, Kubernetes, DynamoDB, AWS EC2, AWS Cloud, Docker, AWS\nCloudWatch, Apac