{"timestamp": "2026-04-14T14:33:11.202231Z", "level": "INFO", "logger": "resume_parser", "message": "SUMMARY\n-------\n\n: Site Reliability  DevOps Engineer with 10 years of\n\nEXPERIENCE\n----------\n\nbuilding scalable infrastructure, automating cloud deployments, and optimizing CICD pipelines across AWS, Azure, and GCP. Proven\n\nSKILLS\n------\n\nin IaC, container orchestration, observability tooling, and security-compliant infrastructure delivery. Hands-on\n\nEXPERIENCE\n----------\n\nin architecting, deploying, and managing AWS Cloud platform and its features which includes S3, EC2, VPC, SNS, RDS, CloudWatch, CloudFormation, Autoscaling, IAM and Route53. Implemented migration strategies for Azure services including Azure storage, IIS, Active Directory, Azure Resource Manager, Azure Storage, Blob Storage, VMs, SQL Database, Azure Functions, Azure Monitor, and Azure Service Bus. Extensive\n\nEXPERIENCE\n----------\n\nusing Google Cloud Platform (GCP) services including Compute Engine, Cloud Functions, Cloud DNS, Cloud Storage and implementing SaaS, PaaS and IaaS concepts through GCP. Created and maintained highly scalable and fault-tolerant multi-tier AWS, Azure and GCP environments across multiple availability zones using Terraform and CloudFormation. Set up Kubernetes (k8s) clusters for running microservices and deployed to production using Kubernetes backed Infrastructure. Developed automation for Kubernetes clusters using playbooks in Ansible. Automated Kubernetes cluster management using Ansible and YAML, deployed Kubernetes clusters on Amazon EC2 instances. Successfully migrated infrastructure automation from Chef to Docker and Kubernetes, leveraging containerization and orchestration best practices to enhance scalability, deployment speed, and efficiency across environments. Leveraged Red Hat Advanced Cluster Management (ACM) to enforce GitOps based policy governance and maintain consistent cluster configurations across distributed AKS environments. Developed and migrated microservices using AWS and Azure services and applied BlueGreen deployment strategies to ensure zero-downtime releases, fast rollback on failure, and enhanced system availability and reliability. Worked extensively with Jenkins and Code Pipeline, CICD pipeline jobs to create end-to-end automation for building, testing and delivering artifacts, along with troubleshooting build issues during the Jenkins build process. Developed Microservices, created test cases and worked with various Python application development and CICD pipeline tools including GitHub, Jenkins, AWS, and Unix shell scripting. Wrote Groovy Scripts for Continuous Integration, used Jenkins to upload Artifacts to Nexus Repository and deployed those artifacts into Docker containers. Used Git, Bitbucket for version control and Jenkins for Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment, ensuring efficient and reliable software delivery. Developed and deployed JAVA REST APIs via micro-services using Docker and AWS ECS and followed Application Test Driven Development (ATDD) to create test plans and code coverage tests. Automated Build for deploying services in Docker environment using Jenkins, SonarQube, Gradle, Groovy, Docker and Splunk. Helped install, configure, and maintain UnixLinux servers on CentOS, Ubuntu, Red Hat. Deployed Dynatrace OneAgent to monitor containerized applications in AKS and EC2. Also utilized Nagios and Munin for legacy system performance monitoring and resource utilization tracking. Set up and maintained web servers using Apache, Nginx and database servers like MySQL, PostgreSQL, ensuring high availability for business applications across development, staging, and production environments. Implemented monitoring solutions using Prometheus, Grafana, AppDynamics, Datadog, and New Relic to improve observability across Kubernetes and cloud environments for enhanced system reliability.\n\nSKILLS\n------\n\n: Version Control GIT, GitHub, SVN, Bit Bucket\nScripting Linux, Python, JavaScript, YAML, Perl, PHP, Bash, Shell, PowerShell, JSON\nCICD Jenkins, Code Pipeline, Gitlab, GitHub Actions, Bamboo\nBuild Tools MAVEN, Gradle, ANT, Nexus, Artifactory\nContainer Technologies Docker, Docker Hub, Kubernetes, Helm\nConfiguration Management Chef, Puppet, Ansible, Terraform, CloudFormation\nVirtualization Tech VMware vSphere, VMware Workstation, Oracle Virtual box\nMonitoring Tools Nagios, Prometheus, Splunk, Grafana, OpenTelemetry, Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana\nAPM Tools Datadog, New Relic, Dynatrace, AppDynamics, SonarQube, Checkmarx\nDatabases MY SQL, Oracle 9i10g11g, DynamoDB, PostgreSQL\nApplication Servers Apache Tomcat, Nginx, Red Hat, WebSphere\nWeb Servers Tomcat, APACHE, WebSphere\nCloud Technologies AWS, Azure, GCP\n\nEXPERIENCE\n----------\n\n: Client: MedHOK, Tampa, FL Nov 2024 to Till Date\nRole: Sr. Site Reliability Engineer\nResponsibilities\nImplemented end-to-endenvironment setup automation using Jenkins pipelines, standardizing application onboarding across multiple client environments. Consolidated manualAWS CLIoperations and ad-hoc scripts into reusable, parameter-drivenJenkins CICD workflows, improving deployment consistency, traceability, and release velocity. Engineered an automatedSchema Compare and Flyway analysis frameworkto scan SQL database migration scripts and classify changes impacting large versus small tables. Integrated metadata-driven table classification sourced fromAmazon S3, enabling DBAs to assess migration risk and execution effort prior to deployment. BuiltFlyway automationto split schema comparison output intoLarge and Small Flyway artifacts, isolating high-impact database changes from routine modifications. Improved deployment safety by allowing database teams to independently estimate execution time and validate large table operations before production rollout. Enhanced schema comparison reporting by incorporatingtable size, index count, and total data volume metricsinto Large Flyway summaries, while filtering out backup and temporary tables using naming conventions such as_backupand_tmp. Ensured accurate execution estimates and safe production deployments. DevelopedJenkins pipelines for AWS Lambda deployments, supporting create and update workflows through configurable inputs such as AWS region, Lambda function name, and source artifacts stored inAmazon S3. Refactored service specificGroovy scriptsinto reusable Jenkins pipeline templates. Created secure, repeatableJenkins pipelines integrated with AWS Secrets Manager, automating creation and updates of sensitive configuration values such as JDBC credentials. Enforced environment specific naming conventions and isolation to improve secrets governance and audit readiness. Built automation forAWS Systems Manager (SSM) Parameter Storeusing Jenkins, enabling centralized creation and updates of environment-specific application parameters. Reduced configuration drift by standardizing parameter hierarchies across QA and production environments. DesignedJenkins based configuration management pipelinesto manage application database property files, including automated backups toAmazon S3prior to modification. Implemented key validation logic to safely add or update parameters without impacting unrelated configurations. AutomatedAWS API Gateway provisioning using Jenkins, consolidating documented AWS CLI steps into a single parameter driven pipeline. Implemented IP whitelisting, environment-specific domain mappings, and stage-level configurations to securely expose internal web services with improved auditability. Developed reusable Terraform modules for private API Gateway provisioning, replacing manual setup steps with Infrastructure-as-Code. Enabled consistent, secure, scalable, and compliant API Gateway creation across environments to support auto-assign deployment workflowswith standardized governance controls. Created Jenkins pipelines for Amazon Cognito app client automation, supporting dynamic scope assignment, environment based naming, and region-specific configurations. Standardized authentication client provisioning for downstream application teams with secure, repeatable, and auditable workflows, reducing manual setup effort. IntegratedDatadog APMacross AWS Lambda and API Gateway based serverless services to capture distributed traces, request latency, error rates, and downstream service dependencies. Correlated application traces with infrastructure metrics to provide end to end visibility into healthcare APIs, significantly improving the root cause analysis. ImplementedDatadog Synthetic Monitoringto continuously validate critical healthcare API endpoints and internal service workflows across QA, UAT, and production environments. Configured multi-step synthetic tests with response validation, latency thresholds, and regional execution to proactively detect availability issues. Built comprehensiveDatadog dashboardsaggregating Lambda execution metrics, API Gateway traffic patterns, error distributions, and deployment health indicators. Enabled real-time operational monitoring for engineering and release teams to quickly assess service behavior during and after CICD deployments. Implemented centralizedDatadog log ingestionby forwarding AWS CloudWatch Logs from Lambda functions and API Gateway stages into Datadog. Enabled log-to-trace correlation using service and request identifiers, allowing faster debugging of runtime errors, misconfigurations, and deployment related regressions. AutomatedSwagger UI deployment using Terraform, enabling consistent provisioning of API documentation endpoints across environments. Integrated Swagger with existing AWS web services to improve API visibility and accessibility\nApplied DevOps best practices by building highly parameterized Jenkins CICD pipelines, enforcing environment segregation, structured logging, and auditable execution. Reduced manual intervention while improving deployment reliability, release governance, and operational consistency across regulated healthcare systems. Maintained secureCICD guardrails within Jenkins, integrating approval gates, structured pipeline logs, and environment-based execution controls to ensure controlled promotions across QA, UAT, and production environments. IntegratedAWS IAM role-based access controlsinto Jenkins automation to enforce least-privilege execution for pipeline jobs interacting with API Gateway, S3, Secrets Manager, and SSM, strengthening overall security posture. StandardizedTerraform remote state managementusingS3 backends and state locking, preventing concurrent execution conflicts and configuration drift during multi-environment infrastructure provisioning. Implementedpre-deployment validation checks in Jenkins pipelinesto verify SSM parameters, Secrets Manager entries, and API Gateway readiness before execution. Added structured validation logs to reduce failed deployments. Collaborated withdatabase, application, and security teamsto align Flyway schema automation, AWS secrets management, and API provisioning workflows with enterprise release and change management standards. IntegratedAWS CloudWatch Logs and metricsinto Jenkins-driven deployments to capture Lambda execution logs, API Gateway request metrics, and pipeline outcomes, enabling faster troubleshooting and operational visibility. Developed reusableGroovy shared libraries in Jenkins, version-controlled in Gitto centralize deployment logic, parameter validation, and error handling, reducing pipeline duplication and improving long-term maintainability. Maintained detailedJenkins pipeline documentation and runbooks, outlining execution steps, rollback procedures, and dependency mappings to support on-call engineers and reduce operational knowledge gaps. Participated inincident triage and root cause analysisfor deployment issues by analyzing Jenkins logs, AWS service metrics, and configuration changes, contributing to continuous improvement of CICD automation. Environment: AWS, Lambda, API Gateway, S3, IAM, Secrets Manager, Systems Manager Parameter Store, CloudWatch, Jenkins, Terraform, Flyway, SQL, Cognito, Swagger, Groovy, Bash, Linux, Git, CICD Pipelines, Infrastructure as Code (IaC), Datadog, Cloud Automation, Release Engineering\nClient: Walgreens, Deerfield, IL July 2023 to Oct 2024\nRole: Site Reliability Engineer\nResponsibilities\nDesigned scalable AWS VPC architectures with custom route tables, gateways, and subnet level access control configurations. Created IAM roles and Security Groups to enforce least privilege access, and integrated Route 53 for intelligent multi-region failover and latency-based routing to support resilient and highly available healthcare workloads. Provisioned EC2 instances across isolated QA and UAT environments using Auto Scaling Groups and Elastic Load Balancers. Integrated S3 lifecycle policies and Glacier for long-term audit storage of compliance artifacts and healthcare logs, while leveraging Ansible for automated server configuration. Automated the deployment of secure, highly available Azure virtual machines using Terraform and ARM templates, incorporating compliance agent extensions, disk encryption and secure access policies. Built reusable IaC modules for provisioning resource groups, virtual networks for applying standardized tagging and naming conventions. Developed Python based automation wrappers for Terraform to support dynamic environment creation and validations, such as DNS resolution testing, role assumption checks, variable input parsing, enabling faster provisioning of compliant infrastructure across development and staging environments. Defined ECS task definitions, IAM roles, and Fargate launch configurations to deploy scalable, stateless microservices for healthcare APIs. Enabled autoscaling, service discovery, and log aggregation using CloudWatch Logs. Built a scalable and modular configuration management strategy using Ansible for EC2 Linux servers, automating patching, user management, service hardening, and audit policy enforcement across AWS environments. Integrated seamlessly with AWS Systems Manager for compliance scanning and secure runbook execution. Managed hybrid configuration environments using Puppet for Linux based systems across AWS and Azure, ensuring idempotent infrastructure state, consistent patch levels, and centralized configuration enforcement. Enabled secure audit trail logging and compliance alignment for regulated healthcare infrastructure. Implemented GitHub Actions pipelines to automate linting, vulnerability scans, and multi-environment deployments for Python and Node.js services. Streamlined approvals, secrets handling, and rollbacks across dev, QA, and production. Applied tagging strategies, budget alerts, and cost categorization in AWS and Azure healthcare environments to chargeback and resource governance models. Integrated Terraform state locking and versioning to prevent conflicts. Architected and deployed containerized applications on Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS), enabling horizontal pod autoscaling, node pool isolation, and custom taints for production grade and staging microservices. Built and versioned Helm charts for Kubernetes workloads, automating deployment strategies for critical services and internal tools. Configured Helm values, parameterized templates, and environment overrides for healthcare specific deployments with clearly separated test, staging, and production configurations. Created detailed documentation for Terraform modules, GitHub Actions workflows, and ECS deployment runbooks. Standardized onboarding for DevOps teams with architecture diagrams, CICD flowcharts, and incident response SOPs. Developed predictive CICD validations by integrating Python-based AI models within Jenkins pipelines to analyze historical build metrics, reducing failure recurrence and accelerating recovery across regulated release environments. Integrated OpenTelemetry agents into AKS workloads to collect distributed traces, runtime metrics, and structured logs from containerized services. Exported telemetry data to Azure Monitor and Grafana for end-to-end observability into healthcare transactions, backend workflows, enhancing performance monitoring and issue resolution. Used Kubernetes Custom Resource Definitions (CRD) to configure sidecars for collecting Prometheus metrics, OpenTelemetry traces, and service-level diagnostics. Applied fine-grained Kubernetes network policies to ensure secure traffic segmentation and isolation between healthcare application domains. Defined and managed AWS ECS services with task definitions, IAM roles, and Fargate provisioning for scalable, container-based deployment of microservices supporting appointment scheduling and claims data APIs. Built secure CICD pipelines using Jenkins and AWS CodePipeline for automated code validation and deployment. Integrated CloudFormation, CodeBuild, and CodeDeploy with static analysis, secrets scanning, and manual approvals to protect sensitive healthcare systems and ensure compliant releases. Established blue-green deployment workflows using Jenkins with automated rollback scripts, health checks, and intelligent route switching mechanisms. Enabled seamless, zero downtime releases for critical services such as patient appointment scheduling, pharmacy APIs, and real time healthcare data interfaces. Created Azure DevOps pipelines with staged approval gates, integrated security scanning tasks, and artifact promotion workflows to streamline release processes. Used Azure Repos and YAML based pipelines to enforce reproducibility, maintain version control, and ensure consistent application builds across multiple AKS environments. Built parameterized Jenkins pipelines to support multibranch deployments with dynamic inputs and conditional execution stages. Leveraged AWS Parameter Store and Azure Key Vault integration to securely inject environment specific secrets into build containers, enhancing automation, security, and pipeline flexibility. Integrated Dynatrace One Agent into containerized applications on AKS and EC2 to capture real-time metrics, distributed traces, and resource utilization. Configured Synthetic Monitoring and Real User Monitoring (RUM) to simulate user flows, analyze frontend performance, and ensure SLA compliance using service-level dashboards. Implemented Datadog Synthetic Monitoring to simulate critical healthcare workflows such as provider lookup and claim submission, enabling proactive SLA compliance tracking.Built real-time dashboards for JVM metrics and error rates while integrating alerting with Slack and PagerDuty for faster response and improved release decision-making. Deployed and configured the Elasticsearch, Logstash, and Kibana (ELK) stack using Chef to enable centralized log aggregation and search across AWS EC2 and Azure VMs. Implemented index lifecycle management and snapshot policies to optimize storage usage and reduce operational costs for long-term log retention. Integrated ELK with AWS CloudWatch Logs to ingest application logs and VPC flow logs, enhancing real-time observability. Automated ELK cluster scaling and health checks using Ansible playbooks, Java based services traceability and audit readiness in healthcare systems. Configured Azure Monitor diagnostic settings and Log Analytics to track user activity, API failures, and system health across services. Integrated Fluent Bit with OpenTelemetry to forward logs to Elasticsearch and Azure Monitor, enabling log-to-trace correlation using injected trace IDs for enhanced audit reporting and observability. Designed and implemented secure, scalable CICD pipelines using Jenkins and AWS CodePipeline, with detailed documentation of automation scripts, deployment flows, and compliance checkpoints for audit readiness. Managed containerized deployments via Kubernetes (AKS), and built production-ready services using AWS ECS, enabling scalable, low-latency healthcare APIs with efficient resource utilization and fault isolation. Applied AI-enhanced monitoring practices using anomaly detection in Dynatrace and Datadog to proactively identify failures and trigger automated healing actions in containerized microservices. Managed secrets and environment variables securely using Azure Key Vault and AWS Parameter Store, implementing RBAC and audit logging to monitor access across regulated systems. Enforced encryption, logging, and tagging compliance using Azure Policy and AWS Config, triggering automated remediation playbooks for drift correction. Automated EC2 and AKS provisioning, patching, and service configurations using Terraform and Ansible, maintaining environment consistency through version-controlled playbooks. Built custom OpenTelemetry based logging pipelines to route logs by severity and application tier for streamlined ingestion, compliance validation, and observability. Deployed enterprise applications on AWS Elastic Beanstalk and Azure App Service by configuring environment settings, auto-scaling policies, and deployment slots. Integrated custom domains, HTTPS endpoints using ACM\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\n--------------\n\n, and monitored service health through environment metrics to ensure high availability and secure access. Environment: AWS, VPC, IAM, Route 53, EC2, S3, Glacier, Ansible, Azure, Terraform, ARM templates, Python, ECS, Fargate, CloudWatch Logs, Lambda, SQS, SNS, Puppet, GitHub Actions, CloudFormation, AKS, Helm, Jenkins, CodePipeline, CodeBuild, CodeDeploy, Azure DevOps, Azure Repos, YAML, Parameter Store, Azure Key Vault, Dynatrace, Synthetic Monitoring, RUM, Datadog, Slack, PagerDuty, ELK Stack, Chef, Log Analytics, Fluent Bit, OpenTelemetry, App Service, Elastic Beanstalk, Azure Monitor, Azure Policy, AWS Config, RBAC, ACM\nClient: Humana, Louisville, KY September 2020 to June 2023\nRole: DevOps Engineer\nResponsibilities\nEngineered scalable, compliant Azure infrastructure using ARM templates and Azure Stack Services. Automated environment provisioning with reusable IaC modules, accelerating deployment timelines, ensuring consistency across environments, and aligning with HIPAA audit and compliance standards. Implemented enterprise grade Azure Blob and File Storage solutions for secure healthcare data management. Created storage accounts, configured for content acceleration, set up SAS token policies, and managed encryption keys to ensure HIPAA compliance and fast data access across distributed systems. Architected and deployed highly scalable and reliable infrastructure on Azure using reusable Terraform modules and ARM templates to provision consistent virtual networks, subnets, route tables, and diagnostic settings, ensuring seamless infrastructure parity across development, testing, staging, and production environments. Built and maintained internal JiraConfluence documentation to standardize CICD, automation scripts, IaC modules, and service ownership playbooks, significantly reducing DevOps onboarding time and audit review efforts. Containerized Java based microservices using Docker and deployed them on Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS), implementing horizontal pod autoscaling and dedicated node pools to ensure high scalability, resource isolation, and fault tolerance across test and production grade clusters. Integrated AI-powered automation to validate Terraform configurations and detect anomalies in CICD pipelines. Reduced manual scripting by 40 through predictive error detection, environment templating, and self-healing logic. Designed a full-stack observability framework using OpenTelemetry, Prometheus, Datadog, and ELK to correlate logs, metrics, and traces across Kubernetes workloads. Enabled RCA and enhanced SLO monitoring with alert routing. Implemented serverless architecture using Azure Functions, Service Bus, and Event Grid to trigger real-time billing workflows and appointment reminders, improving latency and reducing costs for infrequent workloads. Integrated Red Hat Advanced Cluster Management (ACM) for Azure Kubernetes Service AKS environments to centralize policy governance, enforce healthcare compliance, and provide unified visibility across multiple clusters. Enabled consistent configuration management and improved multi-cluster observability across patient care systems. Leveraged Helm charts and Kubernetes manifests to manage dynamic and environment specific resource configurations efficiently. Enabled seamless zero-downtime deployments using Kubernetes rolling update strategies and implemented automated rollback mechanisms triggered by health check failures to maintain application availability. Developed secure, multi-stage CICD pipelines in Azure DevOps for scalable Maven based Java applications, integrating secrets and credentials from Azure Key Vault and deploying versioned artifacts to Nexus Repository. Used custom PowerShell scripts to promote packages across environments and support blue-green deployments. Integrated Jenkins with Terraform and Ansible workflows to automatically provision complete test environments before pipeline execution. Enabled developers to quickly launch end-to-end test beds for eligibility API microservices in under 15 minutes, improving testing efficiency and delivery speed. Integrated GitLab CI pipelines for automated testing, artifact promotion, and provisioning using Terraform and Ansible, ensuring policy-compliant deployments and consistent state management across Azure Kubernetes clusters. Led initiatives to create standardized, version-controlled templates and detailed documentation for ARM, Terraform, and Ansible-based deployments across HIPAA-compliant Azure environments. Created AI-integrated scripts to analyze infrastructure logs and predict scaling needs, feeding insights into Ansible patch automation routines for 500 VMs. Embedded Checkmarx static code analysis into CICD pipelines, configured scan thresholds, and generated compliance reports, enabling secure releases and protection against OWASP vulnerabilities in healthcare systems. Authored end-to-end DevOps process documentation including CICD pipelines, rollback strategies, Helm chart configurations, and secure credential handling with Key Vault and Parameter Store. Deployed OpenTelemetry agents across AKS workloads and integrated telemetry into Azure Monitor and AppDynamics. Instrumented real-time tracing of patient eligibility calls, improving MTTR by 30 for API failures. Built comprehensive AppDynamics dashboards for JVM performance monitoring of provider search microservices running in production environments. Tuned garbage collection settings and optimized connection pool sizing based on detailed APM metrics to reduce latency spikes and improve application responsiveness during high traffic periods. Authored reusable Terraform scripts for provisioning Azure resources, including virtual networks, key vaults, private endpoints, and diagnostics settings with tagging standards. Ensured consistent and reproducible infrastructure deployments across multiple teams supporting high-availability claims and eligibility API workloads. Developed Ansible playbooks for OS patching, VM bootstrap, and middleware configuration across Ubuntu and RHEL workloads in Azure. Enabled patch automation for 500 servers supporting health care enterprise tools. Integrated Puppet manifests within Jenkins pipelines for configuration drift enforcement. Used Hiera and custom facts to ensure system state consistency across on-prem and cloud servers. Created Python automation scripts to seamlessly integrate with Puppet APIs and Jenkins webhooks, enabling batch deployments of Java WAR files to multiple test environments. Implemented automated verification of post-deployment health using API probes, ensuring application stability and deployment success across environments. Maintained structured Git based branching strategies across enterprise GitHub and Azure Repos to support collaborative development workflows. Enforced trunk-based development practices, implemented pull request validations, and code review policies to ensure high-quality code integration with regulated healthcare release cycles. Migrated legacy applications from SVN and TFS source control systems to Git, resolving complex branching inconsistencies and accurately mapping user contribution histories. Modernized source code management (SCM) practices by establishing Git workflows that enhanced collaboration, traceability, and continuous integration readiness. Configured Azure Container Registry (ACR) pipelines for Docker image builds and integrated image scanning tools to detect vulnerable base images during builds. Managed Jenkins agents on Azure VMs with label-based execution for Linux and Windows builds, optimizing performance by tuning JVM heap settings. Used JIRA to manage agile sprints, track defect resolution and ensure timely delivery of key features. Linked JIRA issues to CICD pipeline deployments, enabling complete traceability and compliance tracking across environments. Tuned SQL queries embedded within Java based applications by analyzing slow query logs, optimizing query execution plans, refactoring complex joins, and introducing appropriate indexing strategies. Achieved a 40 improvement in dashboard load times for the provider analytics platform, significantly enhancing user\n\nEXPERIENCE\n----------\n\nand system responsiveness under peak load conditions. Developed Python based batch loaders to process bulk data into Azure SQL and PostgreSQL, supporting data refreshes for claims reporting dashboards. Integrated RESTful APIs with Azure Logic Apps to automate claims adjudication workflows and initiate real-time notifications to downstream systems. Streamlined inter system communication processes, reduced dependency on manual intervention, and enhanced operational efficiency in claims processing pipelines. Environment: Azure, ARM templates, Azure Stack, Blob Storage, Terraform, Virtual Networks, Jira, 