udWatch metrics to ensure availability and performance during peak financial cycles while reducing manual provisioning and improving audit readiness. Deployed Docker and Podman containers across multi-platform Kubernetes ecosystems including GKE, OpenShift, and Rancher. Implemented container lifecycle management strategies, optimized image builds and enforced runtime security policies. Enabled infrastructure consistency and portability across hybrid cloud environments. Developed and maintained Helm charts for scalable deployment of microservices on Kubernetes and OpenShift platforms, incorporating best practices for templating, environment specific configuration, and rollback strategies. Engineered containerized application delivery pipelines on AWS and Kubernetes, leveraging EKS native features, IAM roles, VPC security controls, and CloudWatch monitoring to ensure secure, observable, and scalable infrastructure for microservices deployment across production environments. Implemented custom networking architectures in GCP and AWS with subnets, firewall rules, private link endpoints, and DNS-based failover, enforcing compliance and isolation for high-security financial data environments. Automated the provisioning of Kubernetes clusters using Terraform and AWS CLI, implementing RBAC policies, namespace resource quotas, and integrating DevSecOps toolchains for vulnerability scanning, image signing, and compliance enforcement to support secure, auditable CICD workflows. Maintained CICD pipelines using Jenkins and Google Cloud Build, integrating with GitHub, GCP services, andDatadog APM and logging hooksto enhance build-test-deploy observability. Reduced deployment time by 50 while gaining actionable insights on failure patterns and runtime behavior. IntegratedDatadog agents and Kubernetes monitorsto track resource utilization, pod-level health, and service metrics across GKE. Built dashboards, alerts to detect infrastructure anomalies and application slowdowns in real-