nforce system policies, access control standards, and security procedures, contributing to a stable and compliant enterprise environment. Provisioned and supported web servers (Apache, Nginx) and database servers (MySQL, PostgreSQL), optimizing performance, securing configurations and ensuring high availability for critical business applications. Configuredand administered core network services includingDNS,DHCP,NFS, andSamba, ensuring reliable connectivity, streamlined resource sharing, and consistent network performance across distributed systems. Environment: UNIX, Linux, Nagios, Munin, Bash, PowerShell, Apache, Nginx, Corn, MySQL, PostgreSQL, Yum, apt-get, VMware, VirtualBox, DNS, DHCP, NFS, Samba, Git\nClient: Zoho, Chennai, India May 2014 to October 2015\nRole: Software Engineer\nResponsibilities: Assisted in developingdynamic web applications using theStruts MVC framework, contributing to modular design by separating business logic from UI for better code organization and maintainability. Supported integration of SOAP based XML web servicesto enable cross-system communication, working on data parsing and transformation to ensure consistent and accurate message formats. Contributed to building reusable componentsusingJSP, Servlets, JSTL, and custom tag libraries, helping reduce redundancy and simplify code updates during the development cycle. Worked on front-end development tasksusingHTML5, CSS3, andBootstrap, helping create responsive UI screens optimized for desktops and mobile devices through media queries and flexible layouts. Assisted in creating mobile-friendly web interfacesusingBootstrap UI elementslike modals and forms, improving usability and reducing design time through reusable components. Gained hands-on\n\nEXPERIENCE\n----------\n\nwith Git and Jenkins, participating in version control, code merges, and automated builds within the CICD pipeline for improved collaboration and deployment consistency. Helped configure Maven based builds, learning to managelibrary dependencies, plugin configurations, and automate the full\n\nPROJECTS\n--------\n\nbuild lifecycle by editingPOM filesunder supervision and guidance. Wrote basic SQL queries and stored procedures and worked withJDBCto connect Java applications to relational databases, supporting reliable data access and ensuring functional backend integration. Environment: Java, Java EE, Struts, Maven, JDBC, JSP, Java Servlets, JSTL, SOAP, HTML, CSS, XML, Bootstrap, Jenkins, Git, JIRA, SQL\n\nEDUCATION\n---------\n\n: Vellore Institute of Technology June 2010 to April 2014\nBachelor of Technology Computer Science", "request_id": "cbdae477-4df1-4bcb-b944-1a3c43da9532"}
