{"timestamp": "2026-04-14T16:57:39.727039Z", "level": "INFO", "logger": "resume_parser", "message": "\ud83c\udfaf MODEL PARSED ENTITIES", "request_id": "d861e642-3231-4860-bbb5-1997857f5385", "work_experience": [{"job_title": "Aetna Health  Lead Data Engineer    Present", "company_name": "", "location": "", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": true, "clients": [], "description": "Designed and deployed agentic retrieval workflows using Python, LangChain, and LangGraph to build context-aware agents enabling automated scoring and quality metric computation while ensuring HIPAA-compliant audit trails across AWS S3, Lambda, and Glue. Migrated legacy orchestration from Apache Airflow to Dagster across 40 production pipelines on AWS ECS and EKS, implementing retries, backfills, scheduling, and data quality alerts with Power BI and Collibra frameworks. Built production-grade LLM-driven scoring systems using DSPy, integrating prompt optimization with GPT-4 and Claude on AWS SageMaker, leveraging MLflow for model versioning, eval set generation, and continuous feedback loops under HIPAA-compliant governance. Engineered backend services using Python, AWS Lambda, EventBridge, and AWS CDK to ingest metadata from GitHub and Jenkins, computing quality signals and anomalies exposed through RESTful APIs and Power BI dashboards under HIPAA compliance. Orchestrated large-scale backfills using Dagster and AWS Glue, processing over 10M records with batching, caching, and DSPy-based score optimization, ensuring data quality captured in AWS CloudWatch and Collibra lineage tracking. Implemented SonarQube integration for code-quality scoring, linking static analysis with PR metadata and commit history, building Jira-integrated workflows for epicwork-type classification and automated tagging ensuring HIPAA-compliant metadata governance. Developed AIML pipelines using MLLIB and Numpy to predict patient readmission risk, orchestrated with Airflow for ingestion and model retraining, ensuring HIPAA-compliant data handling, HL7 interoperability, and audit trails aligned with HITECH regulations. JPMorgan Chase  Sr. Data Engineer\nDesigned and deployed production-grade data pipelines using Python and Dagster on AWS, integrating Lambda, S3, Glue, and ECS for PCI-DSS-compliant financial workflows with automated retries, backfills, and observability including metrics, traces, and logs. Built retrieval agents using Python and DSPy to extract historical code context from GitHub, implementing prompt chaining and context packing for LLM optimization, ensuring SOX and GLBA-compliant secure audit trails across financial pipelines. Migrated orchestration from Apache Airflow to Dagster, enhancing artifact linking across Jira, GitHub, and banking systems while exposing quality metrics to Power BI dashboards maintaining PCI-DSS and SOX compliance. Developed anomaly detection and data quality monitoring using Python, AWS Glue, and CloudWatch, identifying deviations from SonarQube and PMD, triggering automated alerts and implementing DSPy-based score correction. Implemented AWS WAF rules and security policies mitigating SQL injection, XSS, and DDoS attacks, integrating CloudWatch monitoring and geo-blocking to ensure GLBA compliance for digital banking platforms. De"}], "education": [{"institution": "KL University", "degree": "B.Tech", "field_of_study": null, "start_year": null, "end_year": null, "grade": null, "source": "deberta_ner"}, {"institution": "", "degree": "CS Engineering", "field_of_study": null, "start_year": null, "end_year": null, "grade": null, "source": "deberta_ner"}, {"institution": "", "degree": "PySpark", "field_of_study": null, "start_year": null, "end_year": null, "grade": null, "source": "deberta_ner"}]}
